very succinctly:

-insult is when you're described as separate which causes you to imagine yourself as separate. 

if the insult is coming from yourself there is no middleman to say it to you, so it's simply just imagining yourself as separate (unworthy, ugly, etc.)

-compliment is when someone describes something they like about you. 

if the compliment is coming from yourself it would be experienced as just love/positive emotion and probably not a mental verbal compliment (people usually dont compliment themselves in their head i dont think)
